text: Alfreds Alslēbens (July 12, 1892 - November 26, 1930) was a Russian track and field athlete who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics. He was born in Rīga, Latvia. He competed in the decathlon. He finished twelfth and last out of those who finished, whittled down from the twenty-nine athletes who began the event. == See also == * Russia at the 1912 Summer Olympics == References == * * Mention of Alfreds Alslebens' death Category:Russian decathletes Category:Olympic athletes of Russia Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:1892 births Category:1930 deaths Category:Olympic decathletes
